where Ci(t) tracks the cumulative number of infections for sub-epidemic i and Ki is the size of the ith sub-epidemic where i = 1…n. Thus, the model reduces to the simple logistic-type model when n = 1. To model the onset timing of the (i + 1)th sub-epidemic, we employ an indicator variable given by Ai(t) so that the sub-epidemics comprising an epidemic wave follow a regular structure because the (i + 1)th sub-epidemic is triggered when the cumulative number of cases for the ith sub-epidemic exceeds a total of Cthr cases and overlapping because the (i + 1)th sub-epidemic takes off before the ith sub-epidemic completes its course. Hence,
